Project Report on Online E-Commerce Website Using Agile
1. Introduction

An E-Commerce website is a platform where users can buy and sell products online. It provides product listing, cart system, and online payment options. This project is developed using Agile methodology to deliver features in a step-by-step manner.

2. Objective

To provide an online shopping system

To manage products and categories

To allow add-to-cart and checkout

To manage orders and delivery status

3. Scope

Modules included:

User login/signup

Product browsing and search

Cart and checkout

Order placement

Admin panel (basic)

4. Agile Development

Agile divides the project into small tasks and develops in iterations.

Sprint Plan

Sprint 1: Login + product listing
Sprint 2: Cart system + product search
Sprint 3: Checkout + order system
Sprint 4: Admin panel + testing

5. Technologies

Frontend: HTML, CSS, JavaScript, Bootstrap

Backend: Java / PHP / Node.js

Database: MySQL

Tools: VS Code / Eclipse

6. Conclusion

This e-commerce website provides a simple and user-friendly shopping experience. Agile helped in building the project in small parts which reduced errors and improved quality.
